description: Tyrrell, Joseph Burr: 1858-1957. Geologist and mining engineer interested in Canadian history; member of Geological Survey of Canada; prominent in surveying and exploring western and northern Canada, 1881-1898; edited works of explorers (Canadian who's who, 1936-1937). // Dowling, Donaldson Bogart: 1858-1925. Civil engineer hired by Geological Survey of Canada, 1885; surveyed and explored for minerals extensively in West; member of Logan Club. // Fletcher, James: 1852-1908. Entomologist and botanist, Dominion Experimental Farms, 1906. // Whiteaves, Joseph Frederick: 1835-1909.
format: 176E p., illus., diagrams, fold. col. maps.; 26 cm.
subject: Alberta--Geology
title: Report on a part of northern Alberta, and portions of adjacent districts of Assiniboia and Saskatchewan: Embracing the country lying south of the North Saskatchewan River and north of lat. 51°6', between long. 110° and 115°15' west
